      type: "Skeletal Muscle Relaxant (Centrally Acting)",
      action: "Acts centrally at the brainstem to reduce tonic somatic motor activity; structurally related to tricyclic antidepressants; reduces muscle spasm and associated pain without affecting muscle function directly; does not act at the neuromuscular junction",
      sideEffects: "Drowsiness (most common — 30-40%), dry mouth, dizziness, constipation, urinary retention, blurred vision (anticholinergic effects); serotonin syndrome risk if combined with SSRIs, SNRIs, or MAOIs",
