        rationale: "Assessing the patient's mobility status BEFORE every transfer is the critical first step. This assessment determines weight-bearing ability (full, partial, none), cognitive status (can the patient follow commands and cooperate?), strength, balance, and equipment needs. Using the wrong transfer method — for example, attempting a stand-pivot transfer with a non-weight-bearing patient — is a leading cause of patient and nurse injuries during transfers."
